==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Indo-European ''*ekwo-'' ‘horse’, via a Germanic form cognate with Latin [[equus]], Old Irish [[ech]] (Irish [[each]]).

====Pronunciation====
[[IPA]]: /eoh/

====Noun====
'''eoh''' ''m'' (''pl'' '''eōs''')
# a [[horse]]



